summary: This is a calendar entry for a scheduled review of physical evidence related to Ghislaine Maxwell at the FBI Bronx Warehouse. It indicates a planned, multi-hour event involving personnel from the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS) to examine evidence.

events.title: Review of Maxwell Physical Evidence
events.description: A scheduled review of physical evidence related to Ghislaine Maxwell, conducted at the FBI Bronx Warehouse by personnel from the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).

keyFacts: A formal review of physical evidence related to Ghislaine Maxwell was scheduled for March 31, 2021.
The review was to take place at the FBI Bronx Warehouse, indicating a federal law enforcement facility was used for evidence storage and examination.
The event was organized by the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS), showing their active role in the Maxwell investigation.
The calendar entry was created and modified in late March 2021, showing pre-trial preparation activities.
The event was classified as 'X-PERSONAL' and given a high priority (5), suggesting its sensitivity and importance to the case.
